<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Australia-Crash     08-07 0100</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Australia-Crash,0107</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four People Die In Plane Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRISBANE, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two small airplanes collided Sunday
over Morenton Bay near this coastal city, killing four people,
according to civil aviation authorities.
   Two other passengers survived the accident, according to Ken
Williams, spokesman for the civil aviation authority.
   He said one of the two Piper Cherokee single-engine planes
plunged into the sea, killing all four aboard, while the second
crash-landed.
   The two survivors were hospitalized in shock and with minor
injuries, said a spokesman at the Royal Brisbane Hospital.
   Williams said the cause of the accident was not known.
</TEXT>
