<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--CustomsSeizure     08-07 0120</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Customs Seizure,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Customs Seizes Ecuadorean Jet in Smuggling Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The U.S. Customs Service has seized an
Ecuadorean jetliner and arrested a crew member accused of smuggling
cocaine, an official said.
   The Ecuatoriana Airlines DC-10, which arrived from Quito, was
seized at Kennedy International Airport Saturday after cocaine was
found in luggage belonging to flight attendant Edwin Patricio
Aguirre, 28, said Customs spokesman Jeff Margalit.
   Officers found 14 pounds of cocaine in a false side of the
suitcase during a routine examination, Margalit said.
   Under the Customs Service's ``Zero Tolerance'' program,
Ecuatoriana faces a potential penalty of $220,000 and forfeiture of
the jet.
   Aguirre, of Ecuador, was held pending a detention hearing
Friday, authorities said.
</TEXT>
