<HEAD>Serviceman Found Guilty Of Murdering Wife</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EXMOUTH, Australia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A U.S. military court found an
American serviceman guilty of murdering his wife and throwing her
body into shark-infested waters.
   Petty Officer Charles Wayne Elmore, 27, of Texas, was convicted
by court-martial Saturday of murdering his Philippine wife, Bella
Fe, at Exmouth in northwestern Australia on March 16. Elmore's
hometown was not available.
   A military prosecutor said Elmore stabbed his wife at their home
after an argument over money. He then allegedly threw her body,
which has not been found, from a pier into the Indian Ocean.
   The serviceman, who faces a maximum sentence of life in prison,
was based at the U.S. military communications base in Exmouth.
   Elmore pleaded innocent to the murder, saying his wife
accidentally fell from the pier into the sea. He told the court he
did not report the incident for 30 hours because he was ashamed he
could not save the woman.
