<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Falklands-Sale     08-07 0176</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Falklands-Sale,0185</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Huge Island Estate For Sale: Penguins Thrown In</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Twelve islands, complete with a country house and
9,000-acre sheep farm, have just gone on sale for $67,600. But the
buyer will have to like solitude.
   The Swan Islands are in the remote South Atlantic British colony
of the Falkland Islands _ off southern Argentina _ and are about
100 miles from the colonial capital of Stanley.
   Included in the price are the three-bedroom farmhouse and 2,900
sheep.
   ``The farm is a real bargain,'' said Ray Burke, assistant
managing director of the Falkland Islands Co. in London, which is
handling the sale.
   But ``you've got to like your own company out there,'' he said
Sunday. ``You definitely need a boat, because the nearest neighbor
is about 30 miles away.''
   Burke said there are a few shops in Stanley, but ``unless you
have a helicopter, you won't get over there much.''
   But it does have its advantages. ``The penguins come for
nothing,'' Burke said.
   The name of the seller was not made public.
</TEXT>
