<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Pilot Killed,0127</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>One Of Belgium's Best Acrobatic Air Force Pilots Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HECHTEL, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of Belgium's best acrobatic air
force pilots was killed when his French Mirage V fighter jet
crashed during an air show Sunday, the Belgian air force reported.
   Major Michel Duvivier, 38, activated his ejection seat before
his plane crashed, but it was too late, the Air Force said. The air
show was in Hechtel, 58 miles northeast of the capital, Brussels.
   Duvivier was one of the air force's top test pilots and
regularly took part in air shows abroad, officials said.
   According to the Belgian news agency Belga, this was the 41st
Mirage V lost by the air force since it acquired 106 of them in
1971.
</TEXT>
