<1ST_LINE>r i AM-People-Makarova     08-07 0336</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Makarova,0346</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ballerina Dances With the Kirov 18 Years After Defection</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eighteen years after she defected from the Soviet
Union, ballerina Natalia Makarova danced again with Leningrad's
Kirov Ballet _ an event she called ``emotional ecstasy.''
   With special permission from Moscow, Miss Makarova, 47, rejoined
her former company Saturday during its London visit to dance one
performance of the pas de deux from Act II of ``Swan Lake.''
   As she took her bow, many in the audience stood, clapping and
shouting, ``Bravo!''
   ``I wait for that moment for 18 years,'' Miss Makarova said in
an interview broadcast minutes before her performance was televised
live by the British Broadcasting Corp. She would have liked to
rejoin the Kirov, she said, if only she was younger.
   After the performance, the ballerina said: ``I was so nervous, I
was shaking, shaking like I have never done before. ... It has been
a very emotional evening _ now I will have a glass of champagne.''
   Miss Makarova defected in September 1970 during the Kirov's last
visit to London, saying she wanted greater artistic freedom and
opportunity.
   She spent hours rehearsing with the company last week and found
the Kirov had new influences and more freedom.
   When she was asked if it was a pleasure to dance with the Kirov
again, Miss Makarova replied: ``It's not the right word, just
pleasure _ it's emotional ecstasy.''
   ``I love the art of ballet, I love my theater, I love Russia and
I love people, and I don't understand why I cannot talk with them,
why I cannot be with them all these years,'' she said.
   ``I think now it is changed. I will go see my mother. My mother
will see my son. ... Any human can understand this moment for me is
very important.
   ``One company has been in my heart all these years, and I never
lose spiritual contact with them. It is the most happy moment in my
life,'' she said. ``It fulfills my own soul.''
</TEXT>
