<HEAD>Hydrofoil, Motorboat Crash; Three Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MESSINA, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A hydrofoil rammed a small fishing boat
off the Sicilian coast, killing at least three people, police said
Sunday.
   The hydrofoil, which carries passengers between the islands of
Lipari and Salina in the Aeolian island chain north of Sicily, hit
the motorboat Saturday, police said.
   They said the fishing boat apparently failed to take proper
precautions in crossing the path of the hydrofoil.
   Six people, all Italians, were aboard the motorboat, which sank
after the accident, police said.
   The hydrofoil recovered the bodies of a 14-year-old girl; and
two men, ages 23 and 39. Two other men, ages 24 and 45, were
seriously injured and hospitalized in Lipari.
   Police and other boats were patrolling the area, about a mile
off Lipari's coast, in search of a missing 22-year-old man.
   No one was injured aboard the hydrofoil.
